page.title: 11AN EAST COKER FAMILY
page.content: Teresa,her parents,two brothers and the cat live in a three bedroomed detached house with a large garden and field.The bus service is infrequent and they need two cars but they all enjoy cycling locally. Teresa's parents work in their printing business in Yeovil;her two brothers attend the local primary school whilst Teresa attends the Park School in Yeovil. Family hobbies include piano, rebuilding two 1933 Austin 10 cars, squash,gardening,swimming reading and sewing.They take part in many village activities including W.I.,Cub Scouts, Guides,Badminton,P.C.C.,and choristers at St.Michael's Church. They prefer to holiday at home and enjoy outings to the coastal resorts. They consider themselves very lucky to live as and where they do.
